<h1 id="content">Sonar.h</h1>

<article>
    
    <p id="articleTitle">File Description</p>
    
    <p id="article">
        This header file handles all sonar data.
    </p>

    <p id="article">
        By using the <code>sonarMinimum</code> and <code>sonarMaximum</code> variables, the minmum 
        and maximum values for sonar readings can be changed. When the number violates these bounda
        ries, the closest boundary will be assigned to <code>sonarValue</code>.
    </p>

    <p id="article">
        Only members which are meant to be accessed, called, or started in the cases of fields, met
        hods, and tasks, respectively, are shown, some members may be excluded.
    </p>

</article>

<article>

    <p id="articleTitle">Field Overview</p>
    <table border="0">
        <col width="285"/>

        <tr>
            <th>Declaration</th>
            <th>Description</th>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>%int% sonarValue</td>
            <td>The last updated value of the sonar sensor</td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>%int% sonarMinimum</td>
            <td>The minimum value the sonar will read, if a number is below this the sonar will read this instead</td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>%int% sonarMaximum</td>
            <td>The maximum value the sonar will read, if a number is over this the sonar will read this instaed</td>
        </tr>

    </table>

</article>

<article>

    <p id="articleTitle">Method Overview</p>
    
    <p id="article">
        <code>%int% updateSonar( %tsensors% sensor )</code><br/>
        Updates and returns the distance the sonar sensor is reading.<br/>

        Updates the value of the <code>sonarValue</code> global variable and then returns the value of 
        said variable. If the sonar value is out of the [<code>sonarMinimum</code>, <code>sonarMaximum
        </code>] range, then it will set the value to the closest boundary.

        <table border="0" id="parameters">
            <col width="250"/>

            <tr>
                <th>Parameter</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>

            <tr>
                <td>%tsensors% sensor</td>
                <td>The sonar sensor's port or name</td>
            </tr>

        </table>

        <table border="0" id="parameters">
            <col width="250">

            <tr>
                <th>Returns</th>
            </tr>

            <tr>
                <td>The updated value of the sonar sensor</td>
            </tr>

        </table>

    </p>

</article>